-- TMO Renewables Plans Cellulosic-Ethanol Pilot Project in Brazil
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-04-12T19:06:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-12/tmo-renewables-plans-cellulosic-ethanol-pilot-project-in-brazil.html
 TMO Renewables Ltd., a U.K.-based
maker of biofuel production equipment, will develop an ethanol
plant at a Brazilian sugar-cane mill capable of producing 10
million liters (2.6 million gallons) of fuel a year from crop
residues.  The pilot project will be built with Usina Santa Maria
Ltda., the owner of the mill, under a joint venture and is
expected to come online next year, Guildford, U.K.-based TMO
Renewables said on its website yesterday.  The facility, in the southeastern state of  Sao Paulo , will
produce fuel for the domestic market and will be followed by a
full-scale industrial plant, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
